{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The traveling-salesman heuristic produces a route that is no more than 1.5x the length of the optimal route for inputs up to 20 stops.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is algorithmic quality inside deterministic in-process code. No real I/O, OS, network, or model output is required. A pure function test can compare heuristic tour length against known-optimal baselines (small exact-solved instances plus benchmark fixtures) and catch regression in approximation ratio.","test_description":"Run the heuristic function on a corpus of deterministic coordinate/distance-matrix fixtures (including adversarial layouts) where optimal length is precomputed. Assert heuristic_length/optimal_length <= 1.5 for each case and fail on any ratio breach.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.72,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The delivery time window estimates are computed correctly from the distance between consecutive stops and the configured average speed for the road type.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real risk is wiring between leg-distance data, road-type speed configuration, and estimator logic. A single-function mock can miss mapping/config integration bugs (wrong speed table key, unit conversion across modules). No external API is inherently required for this behavior.","test_description":"Construct a route with mixed road types and known leg distances, load real speed configuration as used in app wiring, run the estimator module stack end-to-end, and assert per-leg and cumulative time windows match expected values (including unit conversion and rounding rules).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The shift-hours validator rejects a route whose total estimated time exceeds the driver's remaining shift hours, returning the excess amount.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Core failure boundary is deterministic arithmetic/threshold logic in validator behavior. No external dependency is needed to expose off-by-one, rounding, or sign errors in rejection and excess computation.","test_description":"Call the validator with explicit estimated totals and remaining-shift values around boundaries (equal, just under, just over, large overage). Assert reject/accept decision and exact excess duration returned.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When one address in the list fails geocoding (API returns no results), the service skips that stop and optimizes the remaining addresses, reporting which addresses were skipped.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior depends on real external geocoding API semantics and HTTP contract for \"no results\" responses. In-process mocks can hide real failures (schema drift, status/code/body edge cases, retry/error-path mismatches). Needs real API interaction plus service flow.","test_description":"Execute the service against a real geocoding endpoint with a controlled mix of valid and intentionally non-geocodable addresses. Verify the failed address is listed in skipped output, remaining stops are routed, and no hard failure aborts optimization.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate addresses in the input list are consolidated into a single stop with combined delivery items, not visited twice.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Likely crosses parsing/normalization, deduplication, item aggregation, and optimizer input/output modules. A unit test of only dedupe logic can miss pipeline wiring errors where duplicates reappear in route generation.","test_description":"Feed the service an input list containing exact and normalized-equivalent duplicate addresses with distinct delivery items. Assert output has one consolidated stop with merged items and the final route contains that stop exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
